FOR OPENGL:
g++ -o app app.cpp -lglut -lGLU -lGL

FOR GTK3 on linux:

gcc hello.c $(pkg-config --cflags --libs gtk+-3.0) -o hello

FOR regular C:
gcc hello.c -o hello

For C++:
g++ hello.cpp -o hello

for java:
javac -g Foo.java
The g is optional but it makes debugging easier

for python:
no way to compile:
to run programs simply type python main.py sysargv[1] ect..

